{"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppKitBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/UIKitBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/WinUIBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/GtkBackend","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/Gtk3Backend"],"generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The beauty of SwiftCrossUI is that you can write your app once and have it look native everywhere. For this reason I recommend using DefaultBackend unless you’ve got particular constraints. It uses "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppKitBackend","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" on macOS, "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/WinUIBackend","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" on Window, "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/GtkBackend","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" on Linux, and on "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/UIKitBackend","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" on iOS\/tvOS."}]},{"type":"aside","style":"tip","name":"Tip","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you’re using DefaultBackend, you can override the underlying backend during compilation by setting the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SCUI_DEFAULT_BACKEND"},{"text":" environment variable to the name of the desired backend. This is useful when you e.g. want to test the Gtk version of your app while using a Mac. Note that this only works for built-in backends and still requires the chosen backend to be compatible with your machine.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"aside","style":"warning","name":"Warning","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When using ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SCUI_DEFAULT_BACKEND"},{"text":" to switch underlying backends, you may encounter some linker-related missing symbol errors. These are caused by a SwiftPM bug and usually disappear if you run ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"swift package clean"},{"text":" before attempting to build your app again.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Usage","level":2,"text":"Usage"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["...","","let package = Package(","  ...","  targets: [","    ...","    .executableTarget(","      name: \"YourApp\",","      dependencies: [","        .product(name: \"SwiftCrossUI\", package: \"swift-cross-ui\"),","        .product(name: \"DefaultBackend\", package: \"swift-cross-ui\"),","      ]","    )","    ...","  ]","  ...",")"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figure 1: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"adding ","type":"text"},{"code":"DefaultBackend","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to an executable target","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import SwiftCrossUI","import DefaultBackend","","@main","struct YourApp: App {","  \/\/ You can explicitly initialize your app's chosen backend if you desire.","  \/\/ This happens automatically when you import any of the built-in backends.","  \/\/","  \/\/ var backend = DefaultBackend()","","  var body: some Scene {","    WindowGroup {","      Text(\"Hello, World!\")","        .padding()","    }","  }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figure 2: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"using "},{"code":"DefaultBackend","type":"codeVoice"}]}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An adaptive backend which uses different backends under the hood depending on the target operating sy